Series I
Write a program to generate the first 'n' terms of the following series 0.5, 1.5, 4.5, 13.5, ...
Input Format:

The input is an integer 'n' which denotes the number of terms to be printed in the series.

Output Format:

Print the series and refer the sample output for formatting.

Sample Input:

5

Sample Output:

0.5 1.5 4.5 13.5 40.5

Case 1
Case 2
Case 3
Input (stdin)
1

Output (stdout)
0.5

Input (stdin)
4

Output (stdout)
0.5 1.5 4.5 13.5

Input (stdin)
6

Output (stdout)
0.5 1.5 4.5 13.5 40.5 121.5

PROGRAM IN CPP

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() 
{
  int n;
  float x=5;
  cin>>n;
  for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
  {
    cout<<x/10.0<<" ";
    x *=3;
  }
  return 0;
}
